WEBVTT

00:06.374 --> 00:07.624
You got your seat cushion?

00:07.692 --> 00:09.159
Yeah, they're in the back.
Lyle, you got your jacket?

00:09.210 --> 00:11.695
Mom, I know how to dress
for a football game.

00:11.746 --> 00:13.797
You know, whenever we get
there, you're always cold.

00:13.865 --> 00:15.198
He's ok.
Where are the tickets?

00:15.250 --> 00:16.250
I thought you got them.

00:16.334 --> 00:18.051
You said you grabbed them.

00:18.136 --> 00:19.520
If it wasn't for me,
you guys would be lost.

00:19.587 --> 00:21.171
[Laughing]

00:29.213 --> 00:31.765
Lyle, you left
this door open!

00:33.000 --> 00:39.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:42.277 --> 00:46.163
[Wind whistling]]

00:47.332 --> 00:49.550
[Door creaking]

01:01.579 --> 01:04.414
[Creaking]

01:04.465 --> 01:05.966
[Door bangs]

01:12.423 --> 01:14.308
[Gasps] Sam!

01:14.392 --> 01:16.310
Let's go. We're
gonna miss kickoff.

01:16.394 --> 01:17.311
[Telephone rings]

01:17.395 --> 01:18.645
What if it's Jenny?

01:18.730 --> 01:20.230
Call her from the car.
You know your daughter.

01:20.281 --> 01:22.766
She probably just wants to talk about
a new dress she bought.

01:22.817 --> 01:24.534
Come on. Come on.

01:24.602 --> 01:26.236
[Ring]

01:26.287 --> 01:27.537
[Answering machine beeps]

01:27.605 --> 01:31.541
[Crying]
Mom, dad, this is Jenny.

01:31.609 --> 01:33.877
I'm in trouble.

01:33.945 --> 01:36.046
I'm in so much trouble.

01:36.113 --> 01:37.998
I know you taught me
to not be afraid,

01:38.082 --> 01:41.284
but I'm so afraid.

01:41.336 --> 01:44.054
When you get this message...

01:44.121 --> 01:47.224
I'll probably be dead.

01:47.291 --> 01:50.877
So I just wanted
to tell you that...

01:50.945 --> 01:53.797
Oh, God, please,
pick up the phone!

01:53.865 --> 01:55.616
Please!

01:56.801 --> 02:00.354
[Electric saw buzzing]

02:00.438 --> 02:02.689
[Hammering]

02:08.312 --> 02:10.113
[Telephone rings]

02:10.163 --> 02:12.733
[Hammering]

02:12.800 --> 02:15.285
I hope you want me
to come in.

02:15.336 --> 02:16.837
I mean, between writer's block

02:16.921 --> 02:19.790
and my neighbor's construction,
I'm going crazy here.

02:19.841 --> 02:20.991
What's going on there?

02:21.042 --> 02:23.343
I just got a call.
The bodies of two young women

02:23.428 --> 02:26.346
were found in the Elden Street area
in Bristol, Virginia.

02:26.431 --> 02:29.850
They were both tortured
and electrocuted.

02:29.934 --> 02:31.718
Did they make any phone calls?

02:31.803 --> 02:34.304
Yes. But without
the signature.

02:37.442 --> 02:39.726
I'll be there in 20 minutes.

03:11.893 --> 03:14.544
[Footsteps approaching]

03:18.549 --> 03:21.101
[Beeping]

03:21.185 --> 03:22.853
Is that Ellie again?

03:22.904 --> 03:25.605
She texts me every morning
on her way to school.

03:25.690 --> 03:27.024
How's she doing?

03:27.075 --> 03:30.027
Well, she's already got
herself a bff named Jill,

03:30.078 --> 03:32.195
and she thinks
she wants to play soccer.

03:32.246 --> 03:33.864
She's adjusting.
That's good.

03:33.915 --> 03:37.284
Bristol, Virginia.
The body of 25-year-old Jenny Delilly

03:37.368 --> 03:39.202
was found yesterday.

03:39.253 --> 03:41.872
She had been tortured,
sodomized, and electrocuted

03:41.923 --> 03:44.875
before being forced to make
a goodbye call to her parents.

03:44.926 --> 03:46.710
Her body was then dumped
off Elden Street.

03:46.761 --> 03:48.795
A week ago, the body
of Kara Kirkland

03:48.880 --> 03:51.298
was found in the same area
having suffered identical injuries.

03:51.382 --> 03:53.216
This reminds me
of the butcher case.

03:53.250 --> 03:55.418
Why does that name
sound familiar to me?

03:55.470 --> 03:58.588
The butcher was a sexual sadist
that killed 20 women

03:58.639 --> 04:00.607
in the same area of Virginia
from 1984 to 1993

04:00.691 --> 04:01.925
and then vanished.

04:01.976 --> 04:03.810
He tortured blond women
in their 20s

04:03.895 --> 04:05.262
that lived in or near
Bristol.

04:05.329 --> 04:07.981
That was one of Rossi's
old cases, isn't it?

04:08.049 --> 04:09.933
Does he know?
Yes.

04:09.984 --> 04:12.602
[Footsteps approaching]

04:12.653 --> 04:14.270
Some vacation.

04:14.322 --> 04:15.438
Did you get any sun?

04:15.490 --> 04:17.491
I never got any anything.

04:17.575 --> 04:20.243
Prentiss: Do you think
the butcher's back?

04:20.293 --> 04:22.796
I doubt it.
We profiled him as a white male

04:22.864 --> 04:24.931
in his late 40s
back then.

04:24.999 --> 04:27.300
He'd be in his 70s
by now.

04:27.385 --> 04:29.119
Didn't you almost catch him?

04:29.187 --> 04:31.621
In the spring of '93,
we narrowed the geographical profile.

04:31.672 --> 04:34.257
We alerted every blonde
in their mid-20s

04:34.325 --> 04:36.292
in Bristol and the
surrounding counties.

04:36.344 --> 04:40.180
The pressure got so intense,
the killings just stopped.

04:40.264 --> 04:41.798
Well, the Copelands
killed into their 70s.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.133
This could be him
coming back.

04:43.184 --> 04:44.467
It's probably a copycat.

04:44.519 --> 04:45.852
If he's emulating
the butcher,

04:45.937 --> 04:47.437
he could just be
getting started.

